1
00:00:38,771 --> 00:00:42,399
No matter how I think about it,
there's only one way.

2
00:00:42,400 --> 00:00:43,817
NO MORE GAMBLING!

3
00:00:43,818 --> 00:00:45,278
The prosecutor.

4
00:00:46,446 --> 00:00:49,030
- Let's take her out.
- But, boss.

5
00:00:49,031 --> 00:00:52,576
Going after a prosecutor
will make things worse.

6
00:00:52,577 --> 00:00:56,164
- Damn, I knew he'd be trouble.
- Get your best men ready.

7
00:00:56,289 --> 00:00:58,916
So they can do the job
when the time is right.

8
00:01:05,673 --> 00:01:07,300
HILLSIDE CAFE

9
00:01:13,764 --> 00:01:16,057
Yes, she's arrived.

10
00:01:16,058 --> 00:01:18,059
She just went into the Hillside Cafe.

11
00:01:18,060 --> 00:01:20,062
Hillside Cafe?

12
00:01:27,069 --> 00:01:28,529
Come on, pick up.

13
00:01:58,851 --> 00:02:01,312
This is driving me crazy.

14
00:02:14,408 --> 00:02:15,743
Taxi!

15
00:02:16,786 --> 00:02:17,954
Wait!

16
00:02:27,296 --> 00:02:30,298
The Passenger Ship Spy Case,
the Kwon Soon-bok Case

17
00:02:30,299 --> 00:02:33,510
and the suicide in March.

18
00:02:33,511 --> 00:02:37,305
Han Gyeong-wook and Yoo In-gu
are definitely linked to these.

19
00:02:37,306 --> 00:02:40,600
That ship that sank ten years ago.

20
00:02:40,601 --> 00:02:42,186
I was on that ship.

21
00:02:42,687 --> 00:02:46,940
And I know everything about the incident
you're so curious about.

22
00:02:46,941 --> 00:02:51,237
Could Gang Beom-ryong
be the one to solve this puzzle?

23
00:03:14,594 --> 00:03:15,720
Get him out of here.

24
00:03:28,316 --> 00:03:29,899
Prosecutor Gang.

25
00:03:29,900 --> 00:03:31,776
About what you asked last time.

26
00:03:31,777 --> 00:03:33,945
I think I have an answer for you.

27
00:03:33,946 --> 00:03:35,196
Is now a good time?

28
00:03:35,197 --> 00:03:36,741
Oh.

29
00:03:37,742 --> 00:03:39,035
I see.

30
00:03:39,744 --> 00:03:41,162
Yes, have a seat.

31
00:03:42,079 --> 00:03:45,040
Actually, it's a bit too loud in here.

32
00:03:45,041 --> 00:03:46,417
Come with me.

33
00:03:52,423 --> 00:03:53,424
Huh?

34
00:04:15,821 --> 00:04:17,656
Hey, grab her!

35
00:04:22,411 --> 00:04:25,206
Hey, open the door! Open up!

36
00:04:41,013 --> 00:04:43,682
How could you let her get away?

37
00:04:43,683 --> 00:04:46,893
- Why are you calling on a regular phone?
- Hey, Ho-myeong.

38
00:04:46,894 --> 00:04:48,937
It's an emergency.
Get over here right now.

39
00:04:48,938 --> 00:04:50,855
What are you talking about? I can't.

40
00:04:50,856 --> 00:04:54,150
- I'm at a show.
- It's Yoo In-gu's crew.

41
00:04:54,151 --> 00:04:57,862
- They're coming to take out Gang.
- What?

42
00:04:57,863 --> 00:04:59,864
- Where are you?
- I'm on Yeongseon Island.

43
00:04:59,865 --> 00:05:03,243
- Prosecutor Gang is on Yeongseon Island?
- Yeah.

44
00:05:03,244 --> 00:05:04,620
Prosecutor Gang

45
00:05:05,287 --> 00:05:08,498
provoked Yoo In-gu,
and now that crazy son of a bitch...

46
00:05:08,499 --> 00:05:11,335
Look, there's no time to explain.
Just get over here, fast!

47
00:05:12,753 --> 00:05:14,170
You must be kidding me.

48
00:05:14,171 --> 00:05:16,632
If you just stay put,
Prosecutor Gang will die, you idiot.

49
00:05:19,218 --> 00:05:22,179
If we lose her now, it's all over.

50
00:05:38,487 --> 00:05:40,239
Damn it.

51
00:05:47,872 --> 00:05:49,373
Ram her!

52
00:05:51,667 --> 00:05:53,376
- I can't.
- Just do it!

53
00:05:53,377 --> 00:05:54,378
Just one more...

54
00:05:56,547 --> 00:05:57,715
Just hit her!

55
00:06:00,676 --> 00:06:03,345
What are you doing, you idiot?
Step on it already!

56
00:06:17,985 --> 00:06:19,278
Why won't it stop?

57
00:06:25,993 --> 00:06:28,204
Where do these bastards
think they're going?

58
00:06:36,128 --> 00:06:39,714
- Why can't you get past her?
- Damn it.

59
00:06:39,715 --> 00:06:40,841
Shit.

60
00:06:59,109 --> 00:07:00,110
Ram her!

61
00:07:04,323 --> 00:07:07,993
Harder!

62
00:08:06,719 --> 00:08:08,721
Hey! What the hell?

63
00:08:28,365 --> 00:08:30,576
YOU CAN LEAVE DEAD, NEVER ALIVE!

64
00:08:35,080 --> 00:08:36,957
Thank you.

65
00:08:46,592 --> 00:08:49,929
LOSE LAND, LOSE HOME, END UP IN DEBT.
YOU CAN LEAVE DEAD, NEVER ALIVE!

66
00:09:20,334 --> 00:09:21,335
Jesus Christ!

67
00:09:23,671 --> 00:09:25,004
It's a ghost.

68
00:09:25,005 --> 00:09:27,841
Hey, wait.

69
00:09:27,967 --> 00:09:30,677
I think I saw a ghost.
The ghost of a young woman.

70
00:09:30,678 --> 00:09:32,429
You get scared so easily.

71
00:09:33,722 --> 00:09:36,517
What kind of job could be
in a place like this?

72
00:09:37,518 --> 00:09:41,187
Look. She's taking us there to be sold.

73
00:09:41,188 --> 00:09:42,314
I can hear you, you know?

74
00:09:43,273 --> 00:09:46,151
This place used to be packed with people.

75
00:09:46,652 --> 00:09:49,738
- But everyone got chased out.
- But why?

76
00:09:51,198 --> 00:09:52,408
Hey, we're here.

77
00:09:54,618 --> 00:09:57,162
- Just get over here.
- Unbelievable.

78
00:10:02,084 --> 00:10:06,755
They barged in and trashed the place
just to catch one woman.

79
00:10:08,966 --> 00:10:10,883
Where did those people go?

80
00:10:10,884 --> 00:10:13,594
I don't know.
They just sped off in their car.

81
00:10:13,595 --> 00:10:16,473
- Which way did they go?
- That way, toward the main road.

82
00:10:32,281 --> 00:10:34,323
Why is Jeong Ho-myeong here?

83
00:10:34,324 --> 00:10:35,408
Gang Beom-ryong.

84
00:10:35,409 --> 00:10:38,244
Why did he show up?
And at a time like this?

85
00:10:38,245 --> 00:10:40,663
Looked like he was looking for
some thugs and a woman.

86
00:10:40,664 --> 00:10:42,707
Is it Prosecutor Gang?

87
00:10:42,708 --> 00:10:44,959
I wonder if Ma Gong-bok
had a different idea.

88
00:10:44,960 --> 00:10:48,046
That means he came to meet
Prosecutor Gang too.

89
00:10:48,047 --> 00:10:51,591
This isn't the time
to worry about Gang Beom-ryong.

90
00:10:51,592 --> 00:10:53,259
My priority is Gang.

91
00:10:53,260 --> 00:10:55,511
Anyway, there's no way that guy knows me.

92
00:10:55,512 --> 00:10:57,138
- For now...
- For now...

93
00:10:57,139 --> 00:10:58,891
- Play it cool.
- Play it cool.

94
00:11:25,501 --> 00:11:26,794
Why the hell are you here?

95
00:11:27,961 --> 00:11:30,838
- This isn't a coincidence, is it?
- You.

96
00:11:30,839 --> 00:11:32,091
Do you know who I am?

97
00:11:32,466 --> 00:11:35,427
- What the hell is this?
- Tell me. How did you know?

98
00:11:37,471 --> 00:11:40,264
Are you just playing dumb,
or are you really that clueless?

99
00:11:40,265 --> 00:11:43,894
Anyway, I don't have time to fool around.
Get out of the way.

100
00:11:44,895 --> 00:11:47,855
You were looking for
Prosecutor Gang, right?

101
00:11:47,856 --> 00:11:50,317
Hurry up and tell me what's going on.

102
00:11:54,238 --> 00:11:57,241
She's in danger right now.

103
00:12:15,217 --> 00:12:16,218
What the hell?

104
00:12:17,636 --> 00:12:18,971
You're tailing her, aren't you?

105
00:12:19,847 --> 00:12:22,223
I need to see her too. Let's go together.

106
00:12:22,224 --> 00:12:23,307
What?

107
00:12:23,308 --> 00:12:25,434
Are you crazy? Get out.

108
00:12:25,435 --> 00:12:27,436
Hey, you think I want to be doing this?

109
00:12:27,437 --> 00:12:29,564
If I'd brought my own car...

110
00:12:29,565 --> 00:12:32,066
- Think this is a taxi?
- I'll pay you well.

111
00:12:32,067 --> 00:12:34,486
You don't even know where she went.

112
00:12:35,737 --> 00:12:37,865
Are you saying you know?

113
00:12:37,990 --> 00:12:39,032
Hold on.

114
00:12:40,576 --> 00:12:42,953
Seriously, where did she go?

115
00:12:51,044 --> 00:12:53,087
- Yes, boss.
- Hey, Gong-bok.

116
00:12:53,088 --> 00:12:54,714
Can you pull some CCTV footage now?

117
00:12:54,715 --> 00:12:55,840
Right now?

118
00:12:55,841 --> 00:12:59,343
Hold on, the CCTV footage from where?

119
00:12:59,344 --> 00:13:02,722
The Hillside Cafe in Nakwon-ri.
Pull the footage from 30 minutes ago.

120
00:13:02,723 --> 00:13:04,724
Look for suspicious vehicles leaving.

121
00:13:04,725 --> 00:13:07,977
- Vehicles?
- Trace their route and contact me. Hurry.

122
00:13:07,978 --> 00:13:10,855
- What's going on?
- No time to explain.

123
00:13:10,856 --> 00:13:13,192
- Just text it to me.
- But...

124
00:13:15,027 --> 00:13:17,446
I'm so damn busy as is.

125
00:13:18,906 --> 00:13:20,240
YEONGSEON ISLAND, NAKWON-RO

126
00:13:24,703 --> 00:13:29,958
HANMAEUM SOCIAL DANCE

127
00:13:34,087 --> 00:13:35,380
Come in.

128
00:13:37,299 --> 00:13:38,634
Aren't you coming in?

129
00:13:42,054 --> 00:13:43,931
Come on, get in.

130
00:13:53,899 --> 00:13:55,192
Just a moment.

131
00:14:09,456 --> 00:14:10,540
Come on up.

132
00:14:16,338 --> 00:14:21,009
This first floor used to be a supermarket,
and the second was cheap single rooms.

133
00:14:35,482 --> 00:14:36,942
Why is he staring?

134
00:14:44,866 --> 00:14:46,034
Hey, there.

135
00:14:46,618 --> 00:14:47,619
Jesus.

136
00:15:06,847 --> 00:15:07,848
Hey.

137
00:15:08,765 --> 00:15:11,142
This is either a pyramid scheme or a cult.

138
00:15:11,143 --> 00:15:14,729
- Let's get out of here.
- Hey, come on. Lee would never.

139
00:15:14,730 --> 00:15:15,897
Aren't you coming up?

140
00:15:17,774 --> 00:15:20,652
Hey. Can you just tell us now?

141
00:15:21,445 --> 00:15:23,947
What exactly is this place?

142
00:15:24,948 --> 00:15:27,283
You can think of it as
a temporary shelter.

143
00:15:27,284 --> 00:15:28,617
A temporary shelter?

144
00:15:28,618 --> 00:15:32,330
Everyone in there
is in the same boat as you are.

145
00:15:32,331 --> 00:15:36,876
They lost their homes to Heaven Capital
and were thrown onto the street overnight.

146
00:15:36,877 --> 00:15:40,004
Our Dance Club set this place up
to help people like them.

147
00:15:40,005 --> 00:15:44,175
- It's just temporary.
- Wait, a place like this...

148
00:15:44,176 --> 00:15:46,385
...was set up by a Dance Club?

149
00:15:46,386 --> 00:15:50,056
We used to have a few members
in our Dance Club

150
00:15:50,057 --> 00:15:51,558
who had family problems.

151
00:15:53,060 --> 00:15:54,853
- Come on up.
- Okay.

152
00:16:06,740 --> 00:16:08,783
SEVERAL VEHICLES GOT INTO A CAR CHASE
AND HEADED TOWARDS YEONGSEON RIVER

153
00:16:08,784 --> 00:16:09,868
Make your choice.

154
00:16:13,163 --> 00:16:16,416
Trying to take credit
for what Ma Gong-bok sent?

155
00:16:17,542 --> 00:16:18,626
You know Gong-bok, too?

156
00:16:18,627 --> 00:16:21,128
You think I wouldn't notice
pathetic thugs like you?

157
00:16:21,129 --> 00:16:24,799
- Are you sure he checked properly?
- You don't have time to be doubting me.

158
00:16:24,800 --> 00:16:26,802
You said Prosecutor Gang's in danger.

159
00:16:30,347 --> 00:16:32,349
HILLSIDE CAFE

160
00:16:56,039 --> 00:16:59,917
My family's threatening to disown me
for losing our family burial ground.

161
00:16:59,918 --> 00:17:02,587
- What am I to do?
- Well, why did you sign off on it?

162
00:17:02,712 --> 00:17:04,089
You try dealing with them!

163
00:17:04,381 --> 00:17:06,589
Could you stand up to them
when they threaten you?

164
00:17:06,590 --> 00:17:07,592
Shut it!

165
00:17:08,468 --> 00:17:11,430
Back in my day,
I didn't even blink if I got stabbed.

166
00:17:11,555 --> 00:17:13,098
How dare you?

167
00:17:14,182 --> 00:17:16,767
- Mr. Park, we're here.
- Yeah.

168
00:17:16,768 --> 00:17:20,856
Anyway, you have to keep your promise
about getting the family burial ground.

169
00:17:26,278 --> 00:17:29,864
Where is everyone?
Why do I always get stuck with this?

170
00:17:29,865 --> 00:17:33,743
The others all had plans, you know.
And you're the best at this.

171
00:17:33,869 --> 00:17:36,705
They start all this,
then leave me to clean up the mess...

172
00:17:39,374 --> 00:17:40,375
And who are they?

173
00:17:40,917 --> 00:17:42,626
Why'd you bring these stragglers?

174
00:17:42,627 --> 00:17:45,297
I told you about him.
Manager Bong from my company.

175
00:17:45,964 --> 00:17:47,047
Say hello.

176
00:17:47,048 --> 00:17:49,842
This is Mr. Park Chun-sik.
He's in charge of this shelter.

177
00:17:49,843 --> 00:17:51,218
Ah, the boss.

178
00:17:51,219 --> 00:17:54,054
Pleasure to meet you.
My name is Bong Je-sun.

179
00:17:54,055 --> 00:17:55,932
Ah.

180
00:17:56,057 --> 00:18:00,312
The poor guy who lost his house and job
because of his nephew?

181
00:18:02,689 --> 00:18:04,483
Did they tell you what this place is?

182
00:18:04,900 --> 00:18:08,945
- And what you have to do?
- I was told it's a temporary shelter.

183
00:18:10,363 --> 00:18:12,781
That's a nice way of putting it.

184
00:18:12,782 --> 00:18:17,453
We feed and house people
who lost their homes to those thugs.

185
00:18:17,454 --> 00:18:20,665
You won't find a charity case
bigger than this.

186
00:18:21,082 --> 00:18:23,375
And not a single cent from the government.

187
00:18:23,376 --> 00:18:27,087
I'm working myself to the bone
trying to run this place.

188
00:18:27,088 --> 00:18:29,423
And my joints are killing me.

189
00:18:29,424 --> 00:18:30,842
Well, you're doing a good thing.

190
00:18:31,343 --> 00:18:32,843
Right, a good thing.

191
00:18:32,844 --> 00:18:36,139
But do you think I should be
doing it all by myself?

192
00:18:37,098 --> 00:18:38,808
So while you're staying here,

193
00:18:38,934 --> 00:18:42,354
you can help with cleaning, maintenance,
and a little cooking.

194
00:18:43,146 --> 00:18:46,983
- So, it's a kind of...
- You're asking him to be a slave.

195
00:18:47,817 --> 00:18:49,236
What? A slave?

196
00:18:49,861 --> 00:18:51,363
Don't be ridiculous.

197
00:18:51,488 --> 00:18:54,240
We provide room and board.
We'll even pay you a little.

198
00:18:54,241 --> 00:18:57,451
And we're trying to get people's
illegally seized homes back.

199
00:18:57,452 --> 00:18:59,578
Where else will you find
a perfect job like this?

200
00:18:59,579 --> 00:19:01,121
Can we get our homes back?

201
00:19:01,122 --> 00:19:03,625
Well, the number of victims
keeps increasing,

202
00:19:04,000 --> 00:19:06,877
so we're trying to come up with
a plan ourselves.

203
00:19:06,878 --> 00:19:09,797
Hey, you're not actually buying this,
are you?

204
00:19:09,798 --> 00:19:13,384
They're just trying to use you!

205
00:19:13,385 --> 00:19:17,471
- Seriously!
- Hey, who's this little punk?

206
00:19:17,472 --> 00:19:18,765
Hey, old man.

207
00:19:19,975 --> 00:19:23,227
I get that my uncle looks
like an easy target.

208
00:19:23,228 --> 00:19:25,271
You probably think you can
take advantage of him.

209
00:19:25,272 --> 00:19:28,858
He may be, but I'm no pushover. Got it?

210
00:19:30,277 --> 00:19:31,444
Let's go.

211
00:19:31,570 --> 00:19:33,320
Go where?

212
00:19:33,321 --> 00:19:35,448
You want to stay in a dump like this?

213
00:19:35,574 --> 00:19:38,535
- Have some pride.
- What? A dump?

214
00:19:39,119 --> 00:19:43,123
- A dump? This little punk...
- Stop it. What are you doing?

215
00:19:43,248 --> 00:19:45,708
Okay. All right.

216
00:19:45,709 --> 00:19:49,128
We don't need a punk like you.

217
00:19:49,129 --> 00:19:50,754
As far as I can tell?

218
00:19:50,755 --> 00:19:53,882
You're a lost cause.
You couldn't do the job right anyway.

219
00:19:53,883 --> 00:19:55,468
"Punk?"

220
00:19:59,598 --> 00:20:00,849
Old man.

221
00:20:01,850 --> 00:20:02,933
Do you know me?

222
00:20:02,934 --> 00:20:05,769
Hey, Heo Nam-il.
Why are you being so rude?

223
00:20:05,770 --> 00:20:09,023
Uncle, didn't you hear
that old man insulting me?

224
00:20:09,024 --> 00:20:11,568
You're being insulting.
You called this place a dump.

225
00:20:12,319 --> 00:20:13,403
Apologize right now.

226
00:20:14,195 --> 00:20:16,364
Why should I apologize?

227
00:20:18,575 --> 00:20:21,036
You think that's right?
What about this one?

228
00:20:22,287 --> 00:20:26,166
I'm not going to live like a slave
in a dump like this.

229
00:20:26,291 --> 00:20:27,334
You can stay.

230
00:20:30,086 --> 00:20:32,296
Calm down.

231
00:20:32,297 --> 00:20:33,882
I'm so sorry.

232
00:20:34,883 --> 00:20:36,009
I'm sorry.

233
00:20:37,010 --> 00:20:38,510
He's not normally like that.

234
00:20:38,511 --> 00:20:40,429
I don't know what's gotten into him.
I'll go get him.

235
00:20:40,430 --> 00:20:41,473
Man, that hurts.

236
00:20:41,765 --> 00:20:43,058
Hey, Heo Nam-il!

237
00:20:44,643 --> 00:20:45,935
Unbelievable.

238
00:20:46,936 --> 00:20:50,023
They don't look alike at all.
Is he really his uncle?

239
00:20:52,484 --> 00:20:54,110
SEVERAL VEHICLES GOT INTO A CAR CHASE
AND HEADED TOWARDS YEONGSEON RIVER

240
00:20:56,988 --> 00:20:59,156
Earlier, at the cafe.

241
00:20:59,157 --> 00:21:01,992
Those thugs work for Yoo In-gu, right?

242
00:21:01,993 --> 00:21:05,412
Why is that bastard Yoo In-gu after Gang?

243
00:21:05,413 --> 00:21:06,580
You know why, don't you?

244
00:21:06,581 --> 00:21:09,625
Even if I knew,
you think I'd tell a punk like you?

245
00:21:09,626 --> 00:21:10,918
A punk like me?

246
00:21:10,919 --> 00:21:14,922
The enemy who ruined my operation.
The stalker on my tail for a decade.

247
00:21:14,923 --> 00:21:18,175
A Hwasan Sect gangster pretending
to be a convenience store owner.

248
00:21:18,176 --> 00:21:19,259
You...

249
00:21:19,260 --> 00:21:21,970
- You knew all along.
- Stop acting like my buddy.

250
00:21:21,971 --> 00:21:24,516
I could easily toss you off this car.

251
00:21:25,141 --> 00:21:26,518
What did you say?

252
00:21:37,362 --> 00:21:38,363
What happened here?

253
00:21:39,030 --> 00:21:40,699
A car fell into the river.

254
00:21:45,078 --> 00:21:47,497
Could it be Gang?

255
00:21:49,416 --> 00:21:50,542
Hold on.

256
00:21:52,168 --> 00:21:53,169
That bastard.

257
00:21:56,172 --> 00:21:58,049
He's one of Yoo In-gu's men.

258
00:22:00,844 --> 00:22:03,054
What's he doing here now?

259
00:22:06,891 --> 00:22:09,060
Could they have already gotten her?

260
00:22:10,270 --> 00:22:11,437
Hey! Wait!

261
00:22:11,438 --> 00:22:13,313
Hey! Where are you going?

262
00:22:13,314 --> 00:22:15,442
Hey, stop! I'm coming with you!

263
00:22:21,406 --> 00:22:22,699
Nam-il.

264
00:22:24,534 --> 00:22:25,994
- Nam-il!
- What?

265
00:22:28,329 --> 00:22:30,081
You can't just leave like this.

266
00:22:30,749 --> 00:22:33,334
- Let's go back. I'll talk to them.
- Go by yourself.

267
00:22:33,877 --> 00:22:35,253
I'm going to a friend's.

268
00:22:36,254 --> 00:22:37,838
Don't you know thugs are chasing us?

269
00:22:37,839 --> 00:22:41,301
Yeah, and why would that be?
They've already taken our house.

270
00:22:41,926 --> 00:22:45,971
It's because you beat their guys up.

271
00:22:45,972 --> 00:22:47,557
I can't believe what I'm hearing.

272
00:22:48,475 --> 00:22:50,517
Whose fault is it that we're in this mess?

273
00:22:50,518 --> 00:22:51,643
This is my fault?

274
00:22:51,644 --> 00:22:52,728
Who else?

275
00:22:52,729 --> 00:22:55,939
You're always getting into trouble.
You've been held back two years!

276
00:22:55,940 --> 00:22:58,275
And you even lost the house.
When are you going to grow up?

277
00:22:58,276 --> 00:23:00,028
Then pretend I don't exist!

278
00:23:01,738 --> 00:23:03,740
After all, we're not even related.

279
00:23:07,368 --> 00:23:08,911
Nam-il! Seriously.

280
00:23:08,912 --> 00:23:10,455
Hey.

281
00:23:12,457 --> 00:23:15,251
- Are you really leaving?
- Think I enjoy calling you Uncle?

282
00:23:16,127 --> 00:23:18,963
I felt sorry you had no memory
and nowhere to go.

283
00:23:19,964 --> 00:23:21,841
So I was playing family with you.

284
00:23:23,843 --> 00:23:24,844
And Grandpa's house?

285
00:23:25,845 --> 00:23:28,097
It's not your house, but mine.

286
00:23:29,015 --> 00:23:31,976
So stop meddling
and promising you'll get it back.

287
00:23:32,977 --> 00:23:34,854
From now on,
let's just go our separate ways.

288
00:23:35,480 --> 00:23:36,648
Okay?

289
00:24:07,095 --> 00:24:09,555
- Hey, did you find him?
- We were one step behind.

290
00:24:09,556 --> 00:24:12,267
Prosecutor Gang's car crashed
into the Yeongseon River.

291
00:24:12,392 --> 00:24:14,686
It looks like she was
being chased by Yoo In-gu.

292
00:24:14,811 --> 00:24:15,894
You're saying she's dead?

293
00:24:15,895 --> 00:24:17,855
Don't know yet.
They're recovering the vehicle.

294
00:24:17,856 --> 00:24:19,398
Where are you? Let's meet.

295
00:24:19,399 --> 00:24:20,400
No, no.

296
00:24:21,359 --> 00:24:23,193
No, Ho-myeong. Then you should just...

297
00:24:23,194 --> 00:24:24,988
You should just go back.

298
00:24:25,530 --> 00:24:26,865
What are you saying?

299
00:24:29,075 --> 00:24:31,077
Didn't you say you were with your family?

300
00:24:31,995 --> 00:24:33,412
Go back to them now.

301
00:24:33,413 --> 00:24:36,499
I can't go back now.
I have to see if Gang is alive.

302
00:24:36,624 --> 00:24:41,128
They're just pulling up the car now.
It'll take all day to know.

303
00:24:41,129 --> 00:24:44,631
I'll tap into the police radio,
so you hurry back.

304
00:24:44,632 --> 00:24:47,426
The show's already over. It's too late.

305
00:24:47,427 --> 00:24:48,510
Hey, man.

306
00:24:48,511 --> 00:24:51,847
The longer you drag out a fight,
the worse it's going to be.

307
00:24:51,848 --> 00:24:56,019
We haven't even found Gang.
You want to lose your wife too?

308
00:24:59,314 --> 00:25:00,480
All right.

309
00:25:00,481 --> 00:25:02,567
- Call me if anything happens.
- Got it.

310
00:25:45,109 --> 00:25:48,195
- Grandpa. There's someone over there.
- Where?

311
00:25:48,196 --> 00:25:50,280
- Over there!
- Oh, dear.

312
00:25:50,281 --> 00:25:51,574
Go on, hurry!

313
00:25:52,575 --> 00:25:53,952
What on earth?

314
00:25:58,748 --> 00:26:00,374
Miss, wake up.

315
00:26:00,375 --> 00:26:01,834
Can you hear me?

316
00:26:03,294 --> 00:26:05,796
Grandpa, that's not a woman.

317
00:26:05,797 --> 00:26:07,674
He's a man. Look!

318
00:26:45,670 --> 00:26:46,754
Je-sun?

319
00:27:04,355 --> 00:27:05,648
I...

320
00:27:08,109 --> 00:27:09,318
don't remember.

321
00:27:09,444 --> 00:27:11,529
You really don't remember anything?

322
00:27:12,780 --> 00:27:16,117
Your age, your name, your parents.

323
00:27:17,702 --> 00:27:18,703
Nothing?

324
00:27:19,203 --> 00:27:21,706
No. I don't know.

325
00:27:30,590 --> 00:27:34,761
- You don't have a mom and dad either?
- I don't know.

326
00:27:35,887 --> 00:27:39,015
- I don't know if I do.
- If you really don't...

327
00:27:40,016 --> 00:27:42,934
- do you want to be part of our family?
- Family?

328
00:27:42,935 --> 00:27:45,938
I don't just let anyone in,
but I'll make an exception for you.

329
00:27:47,065 --> 00:27:48,733
You can't be my grandpa or dad.

330
00:27:49,567 --> 00:27:51,026
What about my uncle?

331
00:27:51,027 --> 00:27:52,070
Uncle?

332
00:27:53,404 --> 00:27:54,697
An uncle.

333
00:27:56,491 --> 00:28:00,160
- What would an uncle do?
- You have to play with me.

334
00:28:00,161 --> 00:28:01,412
All the time.

335
00:28:03,790 --> 00:28:05,583
You're my uncle now, okay?

336
00:28:07,376 --> 00:28:08,753
Uncle, play with me.

337
00:28:10,630 --> 00:28:14,092
RESIDENT REGISTRATION CARD
BONG JE-SUN, 215 DOYANG-RO, CHUNCHEON

338
00:28:24,477 --> 00:28:26,020
Uncle, are you bored?

339
00:28:27,230 --> 00:28:29,315
If you're so bored,
you can help me with this.

340
00:28:39,242 --> 00:28:40,992
Don't let go.

341
00:28:40,993 --> 00:28:43,913
- First time on a two-wheeler?
- Yeah.

342
00:28:46,207 --> 00:28:47,333
I won't let go.

343
00:29:02,849 --> 00:29:04,100
Where are you right now?

344
00:29:09,188 --> 00:29:10,273
Huh?

345
00:29:21,284 --> 00:29:22,702
Hey!

346
00:29:23,411 --> 00:29:25,704
Hey!

347
00:29:25,705 --> 00:29:27,498
Are you okay? Hey!

348
00:29:28,124 --> 00:29:29,457
Oh, no.

349
00:29:29,458 --> 00:29:31,377
Are you okay? Hey!

350
00:29:32,128 --> 00:29:33,796
Hey!

351
00:29:46,893 --> 00:29:48,143
Can you hear me?

352
00:29:48,144 --> 00:29:50,604
You're okay now. You're alive.

353
00:29:50,605 --> 00:29:56,319
- I'll call 911 for you.
- Don't call anyone.

354
00:29:58,654 --> 00:30:00,781
Hey!

355
00:30:02,200 --> 00:30:03,534
Oh, gosh.

356
00:30:12,877 --> 00:30:14,337
Jeez.

357
00:30:14,462 --> 00:30:17,673
Don't go out of your way to get yelled at.
Give up on him.

358
00:30:17,798 --> 00:30:20,218
With a nephew like that,
would he be any different?

359
00:30:20,343 --> 00:30:24,388
I'm telling you, he's not like that.
He's not picking up.

360
00:30:29,769 --> 00:30:30,811
Mi-kyung.

361
00:30:31,395 --> 00:30:33,146
Didn't you say you had a date today?

362
00:30:33,147 --> 00:30:36,107
I don't know. Don't ask.

363
00:30:36,108 --> 00:30:37,652
Looks to me like you got rejected.

364
00:30:38,444 --> 00:30:40,655
I thought the guy was totally into you.

365
00:30:41,822 --> 00:30:43,156
I don't know, okay?

366
00:30:43,157 --> 00:30:47,035
I may have been rejected in person,
but I've never been ghosted.

367
00:30:47,036 --> 00:30:48,371
I wouldn't be so sure.

368
00:30:51,999 --> 00:30:53,416
Damn it.

369
00:30:53,417 --> 00:30:55,001
O-ran.

370
00:30:55,002 --> 00:30:57,003
Weren't you seeing a show
with your family?

371
00:30:57,004 --> 00:31:01,132
We already saw the show.
I was just dropping Ji-woo off at home.

372
00:31:01,133 --> 00:31:03,969
Already?
Weren't you going somewhere nice after?

373
00:31:03,970 --> 00:31:05,346
Don't ask.

374
00:31:07,223 --> 00:31:09,600
Jeez, things are pretty tense
over here too.

375
00:31:10,268 --> 00:31:13,520
Oh, by the way, Ye-ji,
did the person you were bringing show up?

376
00:31:13,521 --> 00:31:14,939
Is he going to work here?

377
00:31:15,940 --> 00:31:17,190
About that.

378
00:31:17,191 --> 00:31:19,944
He's not answering his phone right now.

379
00:31:32,331 --> 00:31:35,166
She looks pretty hurt.

380
00:31:35,167 --> 00:31:36,960
Shouldn't we take her to a hospital?

381
00:31:36,961 --> 00:31:39,629
Oh, no. No hospital.

382
00:31:39,630 --> 00:31:44,135
No police, no 911.
She kept saying that the whole way here.

383
00:31:46,137 --> 00:31:47,596
I've got a bad feeling about this.

384
00:31:48,139 --> 00:31:50,850
Usually, only people trying
to evade the law

385
00:31:50,975 --> 00:31:53,226
go around saying you can't call the cops.

386
00:31:53,227 --> 00:31:56,022
Oh, my! So she's a criminal?

387
00:31:56,647 --> 00:31:57,648
No.

388
00:31:58,316 --> 00:31:59,859
- I think she's a prosecutor.
- What?

389
00:32:02,778 --> 00:32:03,904
- She's a prosecutor.
- Oh, my!

390
00:32:04,697 --> 00:32:06,906
She said not to call anyone.

391
00:32:06,907 --> 00:32:08,743
This wasn't a simple accident.

392
00:32:11,078 --> 00:32:15,373
In that case,
let's just wait until she wakes up.

393
00:32:15,374 --> 00:32:18,501
If she's weird when she wakes up,
Mi-kyung can take care of her.

394
00:32:18,502 --> 00:32:20,463
Yeah, let's do that.

395
00:32:22,465 --> 00:32:23,466
Hey.

396
00:32:24,800 --> 00:32:27,344
- Bong Je-sun, right?
- Yes.

397
00:32:27,345 --> 00:32:28,803
I see you left your nephew.

398
00:32:28,804 --> 00:32:31,181
I guess you decided to work
in this dump, huh?

399
00:32:31,182 --> 00:32:33,350
Well, it's not like I abandoned him.

400
00:32:33,351 --> 00:32:35,268
As for the job...

401
00:32:35,269 --> 00:32:37,645
- I'd like to give it a shot.
- All right.

402
00:32:37,646 --> 00:32:39,230
Let's start right away.

403
00:32:39,231 --> 00:32:40,857
Don't think about getting any sleep.

404
00:32:40,858 --> 00:32:44,319
You'll stay here and keep an eye on her.

405
00:32:44,320 --> 00:32:47,447
When she wakes up,
you contact us all immediately.

406
00:32:47,448 --> 00:32:48,449
Got it?

407
00:32:49,116 --> 00:32:50,408
Uh, by myself?

408
00:32:50,409 --> 00:32:51,659
Of course!

409
00:32:51,660 --> 00:32:53,453
You brought her,
so you're responsible for her.

410
00:32:53,454 --> 00:32:55,498
She better not end up a corpse
in my building.

411
00:32:56,040 --> 00:32:57,458
Is that clear?

412
00:33:02,171 --> 00:33:04,297
Grandpa surrenders!
Please just spare my life!

413
00:33:04,298 --> 00:33:05,716
Oh, no!

414
00:33:06,967 --> 00:33:08,135
Hey, it's Daddy.

415
00:33:09,345 --> 00:33:10,720
- Daddy!
- Ji-woo!

416
00:33:10,721 --> 00:33:13,765
I'm sorry I came so late!

417
00:33:13,766 --> 00:33:15,100
- It's okay.
- Did you like the show?

418
00:33:15,101 --> 00:33:16,559
- Yes.
- Hey.

419
00:33:16,560 --> 00:33:19,062
- Just getting home?
- Yes.

420
00:33:19,063 --> 00:33:21,398
Daddy, check out my new mask.

421
00:33:21,399 --> 00:33:24,276
- Isn't it cool?
- Wow, it's so cool.

422
00:33:26,987 --> 00:33:28,238
- Daddy.
- Yeah?

423
00:33:28,239 --> 00:33:30,116
Did you beat the bad guys?

424
00:33:31,450 --> 00:33:32,576
Yes.

425
00:33:33,994 --> 00:33:37,914
- But where's Mom?
- She dropped off Ji-woo and went out.

426
00:33:37,915 --> 00:33:41,751
- Where to?
- I don't know. She was furious.

427
00:33:41,752 --> 00:33:45,256
She said she needed to
blow off some steam.

428
00:33:47,258 --> 00:33:50,052
It's okay. Mom will understand.

429
00:34:25,504 --> 00:34:28,382
I'm sorry. I have no excuse, really.

430
00:34:30,301 --> 00:34:31,510
No, I'm sure you do.

431
00:34:32,219 --> 00:34:33,761
Go on.

432
00:34:33,762 --> 00:34:36,223
I'll decide if I'll forgive you
after I hear it.

433
00:34:46,525 --> 00:34:50,070
One of my army buddies
is a guy named Tae-sik.

434
00:34:50,821 --> 00:34:54,239
He came to visit Yeongseon Island
and got into a car accident.

435
00:34:54,241 --> 00:34:58,244
He was panicking and thinking
if he knew anyone on Yeongseon Island.

436
00:34:58,245 --> 00:35:00,747
And I came to mind.

437
00:35:00,748 --> 00:35:03,917
So what could I do?
I couldn't just ignore a friend.

438
00:35:03,918 --> 00:35:07,587
So I helped him sort out the accident.

439
00:35:07,588 --> 00:35:11,383
And before I knew it,
it had gotten this late.

440
00:35:12,384 --> 00:35:13,677
I see.

441
00:35:14,345 --> 00:35:17,264
So your friend just happened to be here.

442
00:35:18,307 --> 00:35:20,558
- And he got into an accident.
- Yeah.

443
00:35:20,559 --> 00:35:23,269
Well, I guess you had no choice.

444
00:35:23,270 --> 00:35:26,898
- Right? You understand, right?
- Yeah, of course.

445
00:35:26,899 --> 00:35:30,777
But I didn't know you had army buddies.

446
00:35:30,778 --> 00:35:34,822
I mean, I didn't see a single one
of your friends at our wedding.

447
00:35:34,823 --> 00:35:36,574
So I thought you had none.

448
00:35:36,575 --> 00:35:40,954
Of course I have friends.
He was just too busy back then.

449
00:35:40,955 --> 00:35:42,872
He called me.
He said sorry he couldn't come.

450
00:35:42,873 --> 00:35:44,582
Uh-huh.

451
00:35:44,583 --> 00:35:48,419
But remember when I asked you before?

452
00:35:48,420 --> 00:35:51,549
You told me you were exempt
from military service.

453
00:35:54,718 --> 00:35:56,011
- I did?
- Yes.

454
00:36:05,020 --> 00:36:06,313
What's with you?

455
00:36:07,648 --> 00:36:11,818
You keep leaving the shop,
you forget to pick up Ji-woo.

456
00:36:11,819 --> 00:36:14,237
It's like your mind is somewhere else.

457
00:36:14,238 --> 00:36:18,116
Even today.
Lying to me about what you were up to.

458
00:36:18,117 --> 00:36:19,118
What are you hiding from me?

459
00:36:26,917 --> 00:36:28,751
- Are you seeing someone else?
- No.

460
00:36:28,752 --> 00:36:32,589
Then what is it? Tell me.
Stop lying and just be honest.

461
00:36:32,590 --> 00:36:35,383
It's not like that.
I'm not doing anything wrong.

462
00:36:35,384 --> 00:36:37,511
It's always the same with you.

463
00:36:39,763 --> 00:36:41,724
If you want to live like that,
just get out.

464
00:36:41,849 --> 00:36:44,434
Yeah. You should just get out.

465
00:36:44,435 --> 00:36:47,062
Let's take some time apart.

466
00:36:49,231 --> 00:36:50,274
What did you say?

467
00:36:51,108 --> 00:36:52,109
So, what...

468
00:36:52,735 --> 00:36:54,652
Are you saying I should move out?

469
00:36:54,653 --> 00:36:56,904
What about the shop?
And what about Ji-woo?

470
00:36:56,905 --> 00:37:00,492
The shop will be fine without you,
and I can take care of Ji-woo.

471
00:37:04,121 --> 00:37:05,246
It's your choice.

472
00:37:05,247 --> 00:37:07,416
Either be honest with me...

473
00:37:08,083 --> 00:37:10,336
or get kicked out right now.

474
00:37:23,223 --> 00:37:25,975
- Why are you here so early?
- Gong-bok.

475
00:37:25,976 --> 00:37:29,103
Why were you asking about the CCTV?
Is something up?

476
00:37:29,104 --> 00:37:30,397
Tell me something.

477
00:37:31,148 --> 00:37:33,817
Have you been keeping tabs
on Jeong Ho-myeong?

478
00:37:34,985 --> 00:37:38,071
Jeong... Oh, yeah. Jeong Ho-myeong.

479
00:37:38,072 --> 00:37:39,864
Did you notice anything suspicious?

480
00:37:39,865 --> 00:37:43,535
For instance,
did he seem to know who we were?

481
00:37:48,248 --> 00:37:50,375
Not at all.

482
00:37:50,376 --> 00:37:54,213
The guy has never even seen my face.
I told you.

483
00:37:54,338 --> 00:37:57,924
That I would forget everything.
I had completely forgotten about it.

484
00:37:57,925 --> 00:37:59,927
- Right?
- Yeah.

485
00:38:00,594 --> 00:38:01,804
Well, that's a relief.

486
00:38:03,430 --> 00:38:05,808
It's just...

487
00:38:06,558 --> 00:38:07,726
I thought I saw him out there.

488
00:38:10,562 --> 00:38:11,814
Oh, is that right?

489
00:38:13,023 --> 00:38:15,983
Well, he lives in the neighborhood,

490
00:38:15,984 --> 00:38:18,862
so maybe you just bumped into him.

491
00:38:20,698 --> 00:38:21,907
I'm gonna head in.

492
00:38:22,825 --> 00:38:23,826
Okay.

493
00:38:34,253 --> 00:38:35,713
What's gotten into him?

494
00:38:37,047 --> 00:38:38,465
When did he get so smart?

495
00:38:44,972 --> 00:38:46,473
NO CALLER ID

496
00:38:51,812 --> 00:38:55,315
- Yes, sir.
- Right. So how'd it go?

497
00:38:55,858 --> 00:38:56,942
With Prosecutor Gang.

498
00:38:57,609 --> 00:39:00,112
- The meeting went well.
- She say anything?

499
00:39:03,490 --> 00:39:06,285
She said she'd look into your case.

500
00:39:06,410 --> 00:39:09,370
That's it? There was nothing else?

501
00:39:09,371 --> 00:39:10,788
Anything at all?

502
00:39:10,789 --> 00:39:11,957
I'm sorry, boss.

503
00:39:13,709 --> 00:39:17,629
No, it's fine. Rome wasn't built in a day.

504
00:39:18,672 --> 00:39:21,091
What matters is what comes next.

505
00:39:23,302 --> 00:39:25,970
I'm counting on you.

506
00:39:25,971 --> 00:39:28,724
You know what I mean, right?

507
00:39:29,433 --> 00:39:33,020
Yes. I'll do my best, no matter what.

508
00:40:02,174 --> 00:40:04,133
Is something wrong?

509
00:40:04,134 --> 00:40:07,846
You should've told me
if you couldn't make it.

510
00:40:09,139 --> 00:40:12,267
Hey, is everything okay?

511
00:40:12,935 --> 00:40:14,393
So...

512
00:40:14,394 --> 00:40:17,063
I'm still at the cafe
in front of the theater.

513
00:40:17,064 --> 00:40:20,567
Please call me when you get this.
I'll be waiting.

514
00:40:27,032 --> 00:40:30,786
OFFICER PARK MI-KYUNG

515
00:40:34,540 --> 00:40:37,125
OFFICER PARK MI-KYUNG

516
00:40:49,972 --> 00:40:54,268
Here's the thing about love.
It always comes without warning.

517
00:40:55,602 --> 00:41:00,315
On a day you least expect,
in an ordinary, passing moment...

518
00:41:00,440 --> 00:41:03,610
It quietly sits down right beside you.

519
00:41:04,653 --> 00:41:07,029
And because it always begins like that...

520
00:41:07,030 --> 00:41:10,826
you may even discover a side of yourself
you never knew existed.

521
00:41:12,244 --> 00:41:16,748
Here's our first song.
"Rebirth" by Yoon Jong-shin.

522
00:41:30,470 --> 00:41:32,179
- Good night.
- You too.

523
00:41:32,180 --> 00:41:33,473
See you.

524
00:41:35,934 --> 00:41:37,603
This is no time to fool around.

525
00:41:38,854 --> 00:41:41,772
- Hey, did you know?
- What?

526
00:41:41,773 --> 00:41:43,232
A police precinct moved in nearby.

527
00:41:43,233 --> 00:41:46,736
Lately, the cops on the night shift
have been coming to the store a lot.

528
00:41:46,737 --> 00:41:49,989
Damn, why did those bastards
have to move here?

529
00:41:49,990 --> 00:41:51,282
What do we do?

530
00:41:51,283 --> 00:41:53,201
At this rate,
we might not find our merchandise.

531
00:41:53,327 --> 00:41:55,954
Damn, it's not like I can put up
a sign that says "No Cops."

532
00:41:56,872 --> 00:42:00,750
Just wait. Every cop I see,
I'm just gonna...

533
00:42:00,751 --> 00:42:02,294
Beat them up?

534
00:42:03,795 --> 00:42:06,005
I'm gonna be a total asshole to them.

535
00:42:06,006 --> 00:42:08,258
I'll make them never want
to come near the store.

536
00:42:27,653 --> 00:42:29,071
Aren't you going to ring me up?

537
00:42:38,121 --> 00:42:40,082
Damn it.

538
00:42:41,500 --> 00:42:43,126
Damn it.

539
00:43:02,771 --> 00:43:04,898
Can you check me out?

540
00:43:18,203 --> 00:43:20,455
Excuse me, where is the microwave?

541
00:43:21,081 --> 00:43:22,457
Over there.

542
00:43:24,793 --> 00:43:26,086
Thank you.

543
00:45:18,490 --> 00:45:19,950
That'll be 1,600 won.

544
00:45:36,049 --> 00:45:37,300
One's for you.

545
00:45:39,886 --> 00:45:42,639
It's just a little something
to say thank you.

546
00:45:43,557 --> 00:45:44,891
I'll be here often.

547
00:46:03,326 --> 00:46:05,203
How am I supposed to take this?

548
00:46:44,743 --> 00:46:45,827
I got kicked out.

549
00:46:46,745 --> 00:46:47,829
Why?

550
00:46:52,751 --> 00:46:56,128
I've been watching
the scene of Gang's accident.

551
00:46:56,129 --> 00:46:58,422
The Yeongseon River's current
is very strong.

552
00:46:58,423 --> 00:47:02,426
It'll take a while to pull the car out
and to recover the body.

553
00:47:02,427 --> 00:47:03,552
Think she's dead?

554
00:47:03,553 --> 00:47:04,637
No clue.

555
00:47:04,638 --> 00:47:06,973
We'll just have to keep searching
and hope for the best.

556
00:47:12,812 --> 00:47:14,064
Are you okay?

557
00:47:15,190 --> 00:47:16,690
I'm fine, man.

558
00:47:16,691 --> 00:47:18,235
This is nothing.

559
00:47:18,860 --> 00:47:21,403
Take it easy.
You're not getting any younger.

560
00:47:21,404 --> 00:47:23,490
And maybe tone down
the street vendor disguise.

561
00:47:24,074 --> 00:47:25,075
Hey.

562
00:47:25,992 --> 00:47:28,619
It's not like I can just sit
in an office in a suit.

563
00:47:28,620 --> 00:47:29,995
Intel doesn't find itself.

564
00:47:29,996 --> 00:47:33,374
Besides, what's wrong with this?
I gather intel and make a living.

565
00:47:33,375 --> 00:47:34,959
It's the best.

566
00:47:34,960 --> 00:47:36,670
Nothing beats it.

567
00:47:37,420 --> 00:47:39,130
You really never change.

568
00:47:39,547 --> 00:47:40,632
Don't you ever get tired?

569
00:47:41,383 --> 00:47:42,384
What, are you tired?

570
00:47:49,182 --> 00:47:50,767
I've been in Yeongseon for a while.

571
00:47:51,476 --> 00:47:53,311
It's been ten years already.

572
00:47:55,313 --> 00:47:56,481
Time flies, doesn't it?

573
00:48:00,944 --> 00:48:05,364
When I first came here ten years ago?

574
00:48:05,365 --> 00:48:06,366
I thought...

575
00:48:06,950 --> 00:48:08,785
I'd be done with the operation in no time.

576
00:48:12,455 --> 00:48:14,039
But that damn Bulgae.

577
00:48:14,040 --> 00:48:17,501
I searched and searched,
but there was no sign of him.

578
00:48:17,502 --> 00:48:19,546
And the receiver was dead silent.

579
00:48:21,923 --> 00:48:25,843
He has a strange accent,
and he's just a bit shorter than me.

580
00:48:25,844 --> 00:48:27,094
His face...

581
00:48:27,095 --> 00:48:29,513
Do you know
how many tourists like that we get?

582
00:48:29,514 --> 00:48:30,724
Seriously.

583
00:48:32,976 --> 00:48:34,728
May I take a look inside?

584
00:48:34,853 --> 00:48:37,647
Mind your own business.
Get out or I'll call the police.

585
00:48:51,911 --> 00:48:53,246
ORAN CHINESE RESTAURANT

586
00:48:54,706 --> 00:48:56,206
DELIVERY RIDER WANTED

587
00:48:56,207 --> 00:48:57,333
- Delivery!
- Hey.

588
00:48:57,334 --> 00:48:58,500
- Hi.
- The room at the end.

589
00:48:58,501 --> 00:48:59,586
Okay.

590
00:49:06,301 --> 00:49:07,469
Delivery!

591
00:49:10,305 --> 00:49:12,557
ORAN CHINESE RESTAURANT

592
00:49:13,683 --> 00:49:14,976
The whole idea...

593
00:49:15,977 --> 00:49:18,645
...was that I could investigate
more freely...

594
00:49:18,646 --> 00:49:19,898
...as a delivery guy.

595
00:49:25,528 --> 00:49:30,075
You're not quite what we're looking for.

596
00:49:31,076 --> 00:49:33,203
I'm afraid we can't hire you.

597
00:49:47,300 --> 00:49:48,384
Who is that?

598
00:49:48,385 --> 00:49:50,636
He's here for the interview, but he's...

599
00:49:50,637 --> 00:49:52,472
- Well, he's a little on the older side.
- Hired!

600
00:49:54,474 --> 00:49:57,393
- But...
- He's hired.

601
00:49:57,394 --> 00:49:58,686
You're hired.

602
00:50:02,023 --> 00:50:03,440
I'm back.

603
00:50:03,441 --> 00:50:05,192
- Oh, well done.
- You must be freezing.

604
00:50:05,193 --> 00:50:06,610
Not really.

605
00:50:06,611 --> 00:50:10,407
- Here you go. Enjoy your meal.
- Oh my, were you cold?

606
00:50:10,865 --> 00:50:12,867
No, not really.

607
00:50:13,743 --> 00:50:16,787
Hey, stop what you're doing
and make the deliveries.

608
00:50:16,788 --> 00:50:18,288
We agreed I wouldn't.

609
00:50:18,289 --> 00:50:21,667
You're starting today.
And Ho-myeong, you can wait tables.

610
00:50:21,668 --> 00:50:23,878
- No, I'm fine.
- I can't have you catching a cold.

611
00:50:24,546 --> 00:50:26,005
But I have a cold too.

612
00:50:30,385 --> 00:50:31,761
Be safe out there.

613
00:50:34,305 --> 00:50:36,641
But the operation...

614
00:50:37,308 --> 00:50:39,811
...kept taking turns I didn't expect.

615
00:51:03,042 --> 00:51:05,544
This is tough, isn't it? Let me help.

616
00:51:05,545 --> 00:51:07,630
I was hired to be a delivery driver,
wasn't I?

617
00:51:08,381 --> 00:51:11,885
- Why do you have me doing work inside?
- Oh, about that.

618
00:51:15,513 --> 00:51:18,682
It's because you're so good at your job.

619
00:51:18,683 --> 00:51:20,142
You've been promoted.

620
00:51:20,143 --> 00:51:21,186
Promoted.

621
00:51:21,811 --> 00:51:23,480
- Promoted?
- Yes.

622
00:51:24,939 --> 00:51:26,483
Promoted.

623
00:51:30,987 --> 00:51:32,489
- Are you crying?
- No, it's...

624
00:51:33,114 --> 00:51:36,034
It's the onions.
Ugh, my eyes are stinging.

625
00:51:36,159 --> 00:51:39,287
No, don't rub them with your hands.
Hold still. Let me...

626
00:51:40,079 --> 00:51:42,457
Hold on. Oh, goodness.

627
00:51:52,175 --> 00:51:53,675
Ho-myeong.

628
00:51:53,676 --> 00:51:56,513
Your eyes are beautiful.

629
00:52:01,142 --> 00:52:02,809
I guess I should peel some more onions.

630
00:52:02,810 --> 00:52:04,395
These onions, huh?

631
00:52:07,857 --> 00:52:11,360
Ah, wait. I can't.
This isn't right. Hold on.

632
00:52:11,361 --> 00:52:13,738
No, we can't do this.

633
00:52:14,739 --> 00:52:17,659
Life, operations...

634
00:52:19,077 --> 00:52:21,621
You never know what'll happen next.

635
00:52:24,457 --> 00:52:27,000
Who would've thought
ten years would fly by?

636
00:52:27,001 --> 00:52:30,671
That's why I told you not to get married,
but you went and did it anyway.

637
00:52:30,672 --> 00:52:34,132
- You regret it now?
- Who says I regret it?

638
00:52:34,133 --> 00:52:37,761
I have never once regretted
marrying O-ran.

639
00:52:37,762 --> 00:52:39,514
Then what's the problem?

640
00:52:41,182 --> 00:52:42,475
It's just...

641
00:52:46,771 --> 00:52:48,064
I've been a little...

642
00:52:49,357 --> 00:52:50,358
worried.

643
00:52:54,529 --> 00:52:56,155
About what?

644
00:52:59,033 --> 00:53:03,413
I'm worried that the next ten years
might just fly by in a flash too.

645
00:53:04,831 --> 00:53:08,793
What with menopause and all that,
she's getting weaker by the day.

646
00:53:09,752 --> 00:53:14,506
Ji-woo is still just in kindergarten.
Our income isn't stable.

647
00:53:14,507 --> 00:53:17,175
When I first had a family,
I was just so happy.

648
00:53:17,176 --> 00:53:18,969
I felt like I could do anything.

649
00:53:18,970 --> 00:53:21,973
But these days,
seeing how fast time is going by...

650
00:53:24,017 --> 00:53:25,310
It's terrifying.

651
00:53:27,562 --> 00:53:33,234
I wonder if I'll be able to
take care of my family properly.

652
00:53:35,903 --> 00:53:37,196
I'm losing my confidence.

653
00:53:41,034 --> 00:53:43,828
Watching you mope like this,
I know exactly what's wrong.

654
00:53:48,041 --> 00:53:49,709
It's because you're getting old.

655
00:53:50,960 --> 00:53:53,046
Hey, who isn't anxious
about the future at our age?

656
00:53:54,005 --> 00:53:56,007
- You feel that way too?
- Of course.

657
00:53:56,758 --> 00:53:58,508
I'm no exception.

658
00:53:58,509 --> 00:54:01,054
You just live with it.

659
00:54:02,805 --> 00:54:05,850
Just think that you've only lived
half your life.

660
00:54:06,851 --> 00:54:09,896
And just keep dealing with
what's in front of you.

661
00:54:10,730 --> 00:54:11,731
You'll get through it.

662
00:54:13,524 --> 00:54:14,984
And another thing.

663
00:54:15,610 --> 00:54:18,905
Don't try to shoulder the burden yourself.

664
00:54:19,405 --> 00:54:21,281
This operation isn't going well.

665
00:54:21,282 --> 00:54:24,368
And with what happened to O-ran,
you're struggling mentally, too.

666
00:54:24,369 --> 00:54:28,538
That's why as we get older,
we have to rely on each other

667
00:54:28,539 --> 00:54:30,583
to get through life together.

668
00:54:31,584 --> 00:54:33,503
Honestly, have you learned nothing?

669
00:54:41,552 --> 00:54:43,179
Which brings me to my point.

670
00:54:44,180 --> 00:54:46,474
Why don't we stop
doing this operation as a duo?

671
00:54:48,101 --> 00:54:50,812
What do you say we recruit a new member?

672
00:54:52,271 --> 00:54:53,480
Who?

673
00:54:53,481 --> 00:54:55,691
Do you still have contacts at the agency?

674
00:54:55,692 --> 00:54:58,986
No, why look so far?
He's right under our noses.

675
00:55:03,157 --> 00:55:06,536
He wants to take down
Han Gyeong-wook and Yoo In-gu.

676
00:55:07,036 --> 00:55:08,496
He wants it just as badly as we do.

677
00:55:09,622 --> 00:55:12,041
Your rival from ten years ago.

678
00:55:12,166 --> 00:55:15,378
Someone who can take a hell of a beating.

679
00:55:17,171 --> 00:55:19,507
What about Gang Beom-ryong?

680
00:55:21,843 --> 00:55:25,596
- That's ridiculous. Are you drunk?
- I'm not drunk, man.

681
00:55:26,180 --> 00:55:29,058
What I said went in one ear
and out the other, huh?

682
00:55:29,183 --> 00:55:30,684
Listen, man.

683
00:55:30,685 --> 00:55:33,061
I'm a National Intelligence Service agent,
for God's sake.

684
00:55:33,062 --> 00:55:35,064
How can I team up with a thug?

685
00:55:37,608 --> 00:55:38,901
Hey, Ho-myeong.

686
00:55:40,111 --> 00:55:42,154
Let's just face facts.

687
00:55:42,155 --> 00:55:44,323
You're about to turn 50.

688
00:55:45,283 --> 00:55:46,783
You're getting old.

689
00:55:46,784 --> 00:55:48,368
Remember the other day?

690
00:55:48,369 --> 00:55:50,579
When you went to see
Yoo In-gu by yourself?

691
00:55:50,580 --> 00:55:53,291
Back in the day,
think you would've failed against them?

692
00:55:55,543 --> 00:55:58,128
You can't just charge in alone
like you used to.

693
00:55:58,129 --> 00:56:00,172
It won't work anymore.

694
00:56:00,173 --> 00:56:02,467
Listen, that time...

695
00:56:03,593 --> 00:56:04,635
I mean...

696
00:56:10,349 --> 00:56:11,976
I feel bad enough as it is.

697
00:56:12,685 --> 00:56:14,520
Why'd you have to bring up my age?

698
00:56:56,938 --> 00:57:00,273
- Welcome back, boss!
- Yeah.

699
00:57:00,274 --> 00:57:02,984
- Any word from Detective Kim?
- Still recovering the vehicle.

700
00:57:02,985 --> 00:57:06,029
Once the body's found,
it'll be ruled an accidental death.

701
00:57:06,030 --> 00:57:08,908
That damn Detective Kim is so slow.

702
00:57:09,700 --> 00:57:11,368
- Kang-sik.
- Yes, sir.

703
00:57:11,369 --> 00:57:15,330
You need to see that bloated corpse
with your own two eyes.

704
00:57:15,331 --> 00:57:16,665
Understood.

705
00:57:16,666 --> 00:57:18,000
Kang-sik, we're almost there.

706
00:57:18,793 --> 00:57:21,461
Find Martial Arts Master,
and it's smooth sailing.

707
00:57:21,462 --> 00:57:22,838
Wait, boss.

708
00:57:22,839 --> 00:57:26,050
About that Martial Arts Master.
I can't find him anywhere.

709
00:57:27,051 --> 00:57:29,761
I can only track his phone to cell towers,
so it's not helping.

710
00:57:29,762 --> 00:57:32,932
- So you're giving up?
- No, I have to find him. It's just...

711
00:57:33,558 --> 00:57:37,728
We should prepare for the possibility
we don't find him in time.

712
00:57:40,690 --> 00:57:43,943
- See? Now you're using your brain.
- Huh?

713
00:57:44,527 --> 00:57:46,903
You're right. We need a backup plan.

714
00:57:46,904 --> 00:57:49,865
Double our men on the day of the deal.

715
00:57:49,866 --> 00:57:52,826
There's strength in numbers.
What's he going to do when we swarm him?

716
00:57:52,827 --> 00:57:55,954
But a large group will tip off Chief Han.

717
00:57:55,955 --> 00:57:59,040
- That's why you said to keep it small.
- Then we'll just use new faces.

718
00:57:59,041 --> 00:58:02,420
- New faces?
- There's up-and-comers in Yeongseon.

719
00:58:02,545 --> 00:58:05,964
You must know some.
Get them ready for the job.

720
00:58:05,965 --> 00:58:10,261
Our own guys got their asses kicked.
What good will they be?

721
00:58:11,429 --> 00:58:14,849
They can serve as kindling
for the Ingu Sect's fire, can't they?

722
00:58:27,904 --> 00:58:31,782
It must be hard to get things done
when it's freezing out.

723
00:58:32,950 --> 00:58:34,243
Thank you.

724
00:58:35,536 --> 00:58:38,330
But it looks like
there hasn't been much progress.

725
00:58:38,331 --> 00:58:41,541
- Right?
- Progress? Are you kidding?

726
00:58:41,542 --> 00:58:45,254
- It's a fool's errand.
- A fool's errand? Why's that?

727
00:58:46,047 --> 00:58:49,090
The current in the Yeongseon River
is really strong.

728
00:58:49,091 --> 00:58:51,551
Anyone who falls in gets swept away.

729
00:58:51,552 --> 00:58:53,346
They don't just stay there.

730
00:58:54,347 --> 00:58:57,933
They didn't find a body in the car.

731
00:58:57,934 --> 00:59:01,811
Probably got washed up
somewhere around Nakwon Beach.

732
00:59:01,812 --> 00:59:04,230
- Nakwon Beach?
- I'm telling you.

733
00:59:04,231 --> 00:59:08,276
If she washed up over there,
she might've even survived.

734
00:59:08,277 --> 00:59:11,405
I've seen people fall from here
and walk away without a scratch.

735
00:59:12,573 --> 00:59:15,368
But they won't listen to me
no matter what I say.

736
00:59:17,203 --> 00:59:20,081
That's how public officials are.
So frustrating.

737
00:59:24,502 --> 00:59:26,629
Keep pulling!

738
00:59:29,548 --> 00:59:31,217
Nakwon Beach.

739
01:00:07,003 --> 01:00:08,004
Jesus Christ!

740
01:00:08,754 --> 01:00:10,463
- You're awake.
- Who are you?

741
01:00:10,464 --> 01:00:12,465
- Wait!
- Who are you?

742
01:00:12,466 --> 01:00:15,427
Wait, it's me, prosecutor lady.

743
01:00:15,428 --> 01:00:17,847
- How do you know my job?
- You don't remember?

744
01:00:18,848 --> 01:00:21,725
- It's me.
- Who are you?

745
01:00:21,726 --> 01:00:23,894
I'm the one who saved you
on the beach yesterday.

746
01:00:25,104 --> 01:00:27,565
- I carried you here on my back.
- Yesterday?

747
01:00:28,274 --> 01:00:30,775
Are you okay? Can you hear me?

748
01:00:30,776 --> 01:00:31,777
Hey.

749
01:00:36,157 --> 01:00:39,284
Wait, you shouldn't get up yet.
Just a moment.

750
01:00:39,285 --> 01:00:40,286
There we go.

751
01:00:40,661 --> 01:00:41,829
Hold on.

752
01:00:45,708 --> 01:00:49,462
Just a moment.
Let me check your temperature. Hold on.

753
01:00:50,254 --> 01:00:51,838
You're at 37.8 degrees.
It's gone down a bit.

754
01:00:51,839 --> 01:00:53,256
Just a moment.

755
01:00:53,257 --> 01:00:57,553
Since you fell into the sea yesterday,
you need to keep warm.

756
01:00:59,430 --> 01:01:01,014
Hold on.

757
01:01:01,015 --> 01:01:04,101
Okay. There you go.

758
01:01:05,394 --> 01:01:08,897
You might feel fine,
but your fever could suddenly spike.

759
01:01:08,898 --> 01:01:10,107
But, wait.

760
01:01:10,775 --> 01:01:13,526
- Hold on, let me get you some water.
- No. Wait a minute.

761
01:01:13,527 --> 01:01:17,697
- Yes?
- I remember you saving me.

762
01:01:17,698 --> 01:01:19,283
But where am I?

763
01:01:19,408 --> 01:01:21,911
- This doesn't seem like a hospital.
- Oh, here?

764
01:01:23,245 --> 01:01:24,330
A temporary...

765
01:01:25,915 --> 01:01:29,125
- ...shelter.
- Shelter?

766
01:01:29,126 --> 01:01:32,337
Man, that Martial Arts Master
or whatever must be pretty scary.

767
01:01:32,338 --> 01:01:35,007
But don't you think you're overdoing it?

768
01:01:36,675 --> 01:01:40,137
He had a crazed look in his eyes.
I think he'll cause trouble again.

769
01:01:41,639 --> 01:01:44,934
The prosecutor was taken care of, right?

770
01:01:45,059 --> 01:01:48,521
Yes, once we recover the body,
it'll be ruled as an accidental death.

771
01:01:57,822 --> 01:01:59,572
If it weren't for this.

772
01:01:59,573 --> 01:02:02,867
It even has In-gu's voice on it.

773
01:02:02,868 --> 01:02:03,994
It's foolproof.

774
01:02:06,163 --> 01:02:09,125
Okay, good job. Good work.

775
01:02:11,127 --> 01:02:12,419
Listen.

776
01:02:13,420 --> 01:02:16,340
If this gets to the police,
I'll be arrested too.

777
01:02:17,508 --> 01:02:19,175
- Mr. Geum.
- Yes?

778
01:02:19,176 --> 01:02:22,428
I want President Yoo
to complete the drug deal safely.

779
01:02:22,429 --> 01:02:25,181
Don't worry, man.
I won't turn this over to the police.

780
01:02:25,182 --> 01:02:26,892
Never, not at all.

781
01:02:27,643 --> 01:02:28,644
Wait.

782
01:02:30,396 --> 01:02:32,231
What do you need this for then?

783
01:02:32,857 --> 01:02:34,733
I'll have to figure that out as we go.

784
01:02:35,734 --> 01:02:36,986
You sure are curious.

785
01:02:38,529 --> 01:02:40,738
Listen, Mr. Geum.
You just focus on one thing.

786
01:02:40,739 --> 01:02:43,283
Rebuilding the Ingu Sect
to be the Kang-sik Sect.

787
01:02:43,284 --> 01:02:44,743
Let's get the ball rolling. Okay?

788
01:02:45,870 --> 01:02:48,664
Yes. I'll make the preparations.

789
01:02:49,039 --> 01:02:51,208
- Okay.
- Oh, one more thing.

790
01:02:56,380 --> 01:03:00,091
Mr. Geum is one ambitious man.

791
01:03:00,092 --> 01:03:01,385
All right then.

792
01:03:04,597 --> 01:03:06,473
He'll make it big in no time.

793
01:04:27,680 --> 01:04:31,809
- Wait, that one's not expired yet.
- Oh. Right.

794
01:04:33,060 --> 01:04:34,979
It's not like you to make such a mistake.

795
01:04:35,980 --> 01:04:40,276
Did something happen yesterday
with the CCTV footage?

796
01:04:44,530 --> 01:04:47,032
Yesterday, I met Jeong Ho-myeong.

797
01:04:49,076 --> 01:04:51,786
You met Jeong Ho-myeong?

798
01:04:51,787 --> 01:04:52,871
Right.

799
01:04:54,123 --> 01:04:59,086
But that guy didn't just know me.
He knows a lot about you, too.

800
01:05:00,921 --> 01:05:02,172
Did he?

801
01:05:02,756 --> 01:05:06,050
- He said he knew me?
- Yeah.

802
01:05:06,051 --> 01:05:08,846
And not just our faces.

803
01:05:10,055 --> 01:05:12,683
He even knows why we came
to Yeongseon Island ten years ago.

804
01:05:13,767 --> 01:05:15,686
He knew about us, inside and out.

805
01:05:20,899 --> 01:05:22,026
Okay, look.

806
01:05:22,901 --> 01:05:24,737
- There's something I need to tell you.
- Go on.

807
01:05:44,757 --> 01:05:47,551
SPECIAL THANKS TO KWON YUL

808
01:06:02,232 --> 01:06:06,195
Listen up, I'm about to make you
an offer you can't refuse.

809
01:06:06,320 --> 01:06:09,489
You're getting old.
You can't do anything by yourself anymore.

810
01:06:09,490 --> 01:06:11,074
I accept your offer.

811
01:06:11,075 --> 01:06:12,492
- Move.
- Out of my way!

812
01:06:12,493 --> 01:06:14,786
That bastard Yoo In-gu is dealing drugs?

813
01:06:14,787 --> 01:06:17,622
- Let's focus on our deal.
- You don't remember anything?

814
01:06:17,623 --> 01:06:20,124
- I have no idea.
- Did you find out who she is?

815
01:06:20,125 --> 01:06:21,585
Mi-kyung is interested in me too.

816
01:06:22,586 --> 01:06:23,587
Should I just lock him up?

817
01:06:25,047 --> 01:06:27,465
- She'll probably just tear it.
- We don't work for you.

818
01:06:27,466 --> 01:06:29,592
- It's over.
- We face them head-on.

819
01:06:29,593 --> 01:06:32,805
- Are you sure you can take them down?
- I'll find a way.
